<HEADLINE>
<P>
NAVY TERM FOR 'KILLING' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Once again, the Navy and government officials have come up with another 
politically correct word for killing things. 
</P>
<P>
 I refer to the Article of Feb. 2 on the OK for the Navy to detonate thousands 
of pounds of explosives off the Channel Islands. Their new word for killing 
whales and other federally protected species is incidental take.  
</P>
<P>
 During the ex-President George Bush-sponsored war in Iraq, the word for 
killing innocent civilians was collateral damage . Why can't the Navy just say 
they are going to kill things? 
</P>
<P>
 Robert H. Launius 
</P>
<P>
 Channel Islands Harbor 
