<HEADLINE>
<P>
NWS RADAR DEBATE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 I am really tired of hearing and reading about the hypocritical elitists of 
the Ojai area. 
</P>
<P>
 Now it is the National Weather Service radar installation on Sulphur 
Mountain.These individuals complaining about the installation most likely 
receive far more radiation exposure from their television sets (probably big 
screen TVs) and natural background radiation than what they would ever receive 
from the NWS radar tower. 
</P>
<P>
 What is more ridiculous is that our Board of Supervisors is placating these 
individuals. The board is asking that this facility be moved to an unpopulated 
area. Politically, it would seem to be the right thing to do. 
</P>
<P>
 On the same theme, the supervisors will be considering extension of the 
Bailard Landfill. The Bailard Landfill will have a far greater environmental 
impact on the population of Oxnard and Ventura than the NWS radar perceived 
impact on Ojai. If we take the board position on the NWS installation, it would 
appear that the board will request that the Bailard Landfill extension be 
denied and moved to an unpopulated area of the county. 
</P>
<P>
 There are more pressing issues that the board should be spending time on. This 
is not one of them. 
</P>
<P>
 Brent Backus 
</P>
<P>
 Ventura 
</P>
