<HEADLINE>
<P>
LOOKING TO COMPUTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 With computer capabilities, it would be possible to produce through cross 
reference of payrolls and their employee data, an introduction service to 
people who would like to share rides to and from work. 
</P>
<P>
 Through this cross-reference process, computers could print out the names of 
people, their addresses and phone numbers of those working in the same ZIP 
codes and living in the same ZIP codes. 
</P>
<P>
 This introduction service matchup would then enable people to team up and 
share rides, thereby helping to relieve the crisis caused by the earthquake. 
</P>
<P>
 Jack Moran 
</P>
<P>
 Oxnard 
</P>
</TEXT>
