<TEXT>
<P>
 PCC Group Inc.: The Brea microcomputer wholesaler reported first-quarter 
earnings Monday of $135,000, a 70% drop compared to the same period last fiscal 
year, when the company had $458,000 in earnings. 
</P>
<P>
 The company said its earnings per share were 4 cents for the quarter ended 
Dec. 31, compared to 21 cents a share in the same period last year.It came on 
revenues of $15.9 million, a nearly 39% reduction over the $25.8 million 
reported in the first quarter of last fiscal year. 
</P>
<P>
 PCC blamed the earnings decrease on lower sales volume, tighter profit margins 
and high interest costs because of unplanned borrowing. The reduction in 
revenue was blamed on downsizing and a corporate diversification program 
initiated in June, 1993. 
</P>
