<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: LOS ANGELES; NEW BUS 
LINE OPENS FROM LAX TO DOWNTOWN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A new bus line between Los Angeles International Airport and Downtown Los 
Angeles started Monday, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 Line 646, which will operate every 20 minutes in both directions, was created 
to help improve public transportation after the Northridge earthquake. 
</P>
<P>
 The route begins at the City Bus Center at the airport, then goes along 
Sepulveda Boulevard and Imperial Highway before stopping at the parking lot for 
the future Green Line Aviation station near Aviation Boulevard and 116th 
Street. Buses continue nonstop on the Century and the Harbor freeways to 
Downtown, where they will stop along Flower and Figueroa streets until reaching 
Union Station. 
</P>
<P>
 One-way fare is $1.50. Metrolink pass-holders pay 40 cents. 
</P>
</TEXT>
