<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: SAN PEDRO; GUNMAN 
KILLED BY OFFICER AFTER 3-HOUR STANDOFF 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 After a three-hour standoff, a 29-year-old San Pedro man was shot and killed 
by a Los Angeles Police Department officer Monday after he came out of his 
apartment waving a handgun, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Ernesto (Ernie) Frank Aurelio, who lived with his parents in the 1300 block of 
South Leland Street, was pronounced dead at the scene after being hit by a 
single shotgun round.No other shots were fired. 
</P>
<P>
 LAPD spokesman Lt. John Dunkin said officers were called about 11 a.m. by 
Aurelio's parents, who said their son had not slept since Friday and was acting 
strangely. Neighbors and friends said Aurelio had a history of drug use, and 
had recently attended a drug rehabilitation program. Police said he had two 
handguns registered in his name. 
</P>
<P>
 Police evacuated the apartment building. About 2 p.m., Aurelio came out the 
apartment's front door, shirtless and holding a 9-millimeter semiautomatic 
handgun. When he pointed the weapon in the officers' direction, Dunkin said, 
one officer fired, killing him. 
</P>
</TEXT>
