<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: SANTA ANA; COLLEGE WILL OFFER GUN SAFETY SEMINAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Rancho Santiago College will offer a handgun safety seminar Wednesday night 
designed for anyone at least 18 years old who plans to purchase a handgun. 
</P>
<P>
 The seminar will cover safety rules, how to load and unload the weapon and how 
to identify its parts. It will also prepare students for shooting practice on a 
range, which is not part of the seminar, said spokesman Dale Ruhe. 
</P>
<P>
 The seminar will be held in Room U-204A of the campus, at 17th and Bristol 
streets. Instruction will run from 6 to 9 p.m. Weapons should not be brought to 
class, Ruhe said. 
</P>
<P>
 The fee for the seminar is $25. For more information or to register, call 
(714) 564-6220. 
