DOWNED PLANE MAY HAVE BEEN FROM O.C. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By from Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The wreckage of a small plane believed to have flown out of Orange County was 
found in rugged mountains near here early Monday, the El Dorado County 
Sheriff's Department said. 
</P>
<P>
 Rescue crews reached the crash site and recovered the body of the pilot, who 
was alone in the craft. 
</P>
<P>
 The victim's name was withheld pending positive identification. 
</P>
<P>
 Orange County deputies said they had received similar information but were 
waiting for fingerprint confirmation of the man's identity. 
</P>
<P>
