<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD IN BRIEF; GHANA; 500 DIE AS ETHNIC FIGHTING SPREADS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 More than 500 people have been killed in ethnic fighting that has spread 
across northern Ghana, military sources said.Thousands have been made homeless 
in the violence, which erupted Feb. 3, the sources added. One military source 
said the fighting between ethnic Kokombas and Nanumbas has spread to seven 
districts and engulfed other tribes. The Kokombas, settlers from Togo, have a 
history of clashes with the land-owning Nanumbas. They are now demanding 
paramount chief status, which would entitle them to own land as well. The other 
tribes' refusal to give in to their demands has been the main reason for 
conflict. 
</P>
