<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The results of the competing tender offers for Paramount Communications are to 
be announced at 9 a.m. EST today. 
</P>
<P>
 The stock market bet on Viacom Monday, pushing Paramount and Viacom stock 
lower and QVC Network's price higher. The company perceived as the winner in 
the bidding has seen its stock fall because of the debt and other obligations 
it would assume. 
</P>
<P>
 Paramount shares fell 87.5 cents to $76 on the New York Stock Exchange. Viacom 
Class B shares fell $1.75 to $29.875 on the American Stock Exchange and QVC 
stock rose $1.625 to $48.50 on the Nasdaq market. 
