REGIONAL EARNINGS: PERFECTDATA REPORTS LOSS IN 3RD QUARTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 PerfectData Corp., a maker of computer and office-care products, reported 
losses in its latest quarter, and nine months, on lower revenue. 
</P>
<P>
 The company blamed the results on inventory write-downs, a restructuring of 
its sales organization, and costs of new product development. 
</P>
<P>
 In its fiscal third quarter ended Dec. 31, PerfectData lost $141,000, in 
contrast with a year-earlier profit of $102,000. Revenue fell 12%, to $1.7 
million from $1.92 million. 
</P>
<P>
 For the nine months, the company reported a loss of $297,000, while its 
revenue dropped 9%, to $5.19 million. A year before, it earned $342,000 on 
$5.72 million in revenue. 
