<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: PERCEPTRONICS SHOWS PROFIT OF $749,724 IN 3RD QUARTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Perceptronics Inc., a Woodland Hills developer of computer-simulation software 
used for military and commercial training, reported fiscal third-quarter and 
nine-month profits, despite its revenue falling by more than half. 
</P>
<P>
 The company said it managed the profits because it paid off 40% of its 
long-term debt, resulting in a one-time gain of $1.37 million. 
</P>
<P>
 In its fiscal third quarter that ended Dec. 31, Perceptronics earned $749,724, 
in contrast with a year-earlier loss of $1.95 million. Its revenue in the 
latest quarter was $721,360, down 58% from $1.71 million in revenue a year 
before. 
</P>
<P>
 For the nine months, the company reported a $174,824 profit, and a 58% drop in 
revenue to $4.04 million. A year earlier, it lost $4.85 million on $9.5 million 
in revenue. 
</P>
<P>
 Perceptronics said its revenues fell because of a temporary suspension of 
production on one of its software products. 
</P>
