BANK OF A. LEVY REOPENS QUAKE-DAMAGED BRANCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Bank of A. Levy has reopened its branch in Santa Susana, which was closed 
because of damage suffered during the Jan. 17 earthquake. The branch reopened 
on Monday and is located at 3907 Cochran St. 
