<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: INSURANCE AUTO POSTS GAINS IN PROFIT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Insurance Auto Auctions Inc., which sells salvaged autos, reported higher 
earnings and revenue in its latest fourth quarter and for the year. 
</P>
<P>
 In the three months that ended Dec. 31, Insurance Auto had net income of $1.69 
million, a 26% increase from a $1.33-million profit a year earlier. Its revenue 
rose 62%, to $27.9 million from $17.2 million. 
</P>
<P>
 For the year, the company earned $6.62 million, a 51% gain from its $4.38 
million in net income in 1992. Its 1993 revenue totaled $104.1 million, up 72% 
from $60.5 million in revenue in the previous year. 
</P>
