<P>
VENTURA COUNTY REVIEW / JACK SEARLES: METAL BELLOWS IN MOORPARK IS FOR SALE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Jack Searles 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The parent of Metal Bellows-Moorpark Division, a producer of parts for 
aerospace and heavy industry, is negotiating with several potential buyers of 
the Ventura County concern. 
</P>
<P>
 Metal Bellows is part of Parker Hannifin Corp., a Cleveland-based maker of 
industrial and aerospace control devices. 
</P>
<P>
 "We're talking to a number of parties, but no deal has been made," said Cheryl 
Morosco, a spokeswoman for Parker Hannifin's aerospace group. She said Metal 
Bellows-Moorpark has 120 employees producing bellows, hoses, ducting and other 
products. 
</P>
<P>
 The Moorpark firm is for sale because the parent company is downsizing its 
involvement in aerospace, Morosco said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
