<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST VALLEY FOCUS: CHAMBER TO GET OWN CABLE TV SHOW 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GEOFFREY MOHAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The San Fernando Chamber of Commerce will merge onto the information 
superhighway -- albeit in the slow lane -- with its own cable-access television 
show. 
</P>
<P>
 Conan O'Brien was booked and Chevy Chase unavailable, so chamber member Brad 
Buckley tapped his wife, Danielle Sullivan, for the host position on the show, 
which will feature local politicians, pundits and business owners. 
</P>
<P>
 "It's one of those things where I'm familiar with her work -- obviously -- 
and, biases aside, she does good work," said Buckley, who heads the chamber's 
business improvement committee. 
</P>
<P>
 Sullivan hosts a radio talk show on KMGX, Magic FM, Sundays at 7 a.m., and 
hosts a cable show once a month, Buckley said. 
</P>
<P>
 Continental Cablevision, which will grant the chamber free air and studio 
time, has not picked a slot for the show, so Buckley has no idea if he will 
compete with shows such as "Married With Children" or a Soloflex infomercial. 
"The idea behind the show is to promote the city, not only to residents, but 
people who live outside the boundaries," Buckley said. "We want to enhance the 
city's image. A lot of people don't know about the city and what it has to 
offer." 
</P>
<P>
 The chamber will spend six weeks training a crew, then begin airing its 13 
shows in April, Buckley said. GEOFFREY MOHAN 
</P>
</TEXT>
